the first test AND the second test both run, causing double reservations. That's why tests after the first one fail with \"Insufficient stock\" — stock gets reserved twice.\n\n4. **Bug 4 - `OrderRepository.update` doesn't merge** (`src/orders/repository.ts:38`): `update()` creates `{ ...updates, id, updatedAt }` instead of `{ ...existing, ...updates, updatedAt }`. This loses existing fields.\n\n5. **Bug 5 - `cancelOrder` fails because `order.items` is undefined**: This is a consequence of Bug 4. When `createOrder` calls `repo.update(id, { status: 'confirmed', total: payment.amount })`, the broken `update` discards `items`, `customerId`, etc. Then `cancelOrder` tries `order.items.map(...)` on undefined.\n\n6. **Bug 6 - Refund 30-day boundary** (`src/orders/service.ts:99`): Uses `>=` instead of `>` for the comparison. Day 30 exactly should still allow refund (test expects it), but `>= 30` rejects it.\n\nNow let me fix all bugs."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6130,"cache_read_input_tokens":30326,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6130},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5b79c099-0d59-498c-a1f4-3869b59854bd","uuid":"31784373-e300-4cab-9ab1-546cd869f0d0"}
